icks of bats, as opposed to bartonellae. Two tick-borne zoonotic pathogens (R. helvetica and A. phagocytophilum) have been detected for the first time in bat ticks. The present findings add Asia (China) to the geographical range of R. lusitaniae, as well as indicate the occurrence of R. hoogstraalii in South Africa. This is also the first molecular evidence for the autochthonous occurrence of a R. africae-like genotype in Europe. Bat haemoplasmas, which are closely related to haemoplasmas previously identified in bats in Spain and to \"Candidatus Mycoplasma haemohominis\", are reported here for the first time from Central Europe and from any bat tick.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Hornok, S\u00e1ndor", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Sz\u0151ke, Krisztina", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Meli, Marina L.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "S\u00e1ndor, Attila D.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "G\u00f6rf\u00f6l, Tam\u00e1s", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Est\u00f3k, P\u00e9ter", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Wang, Yuanzhi", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Tu, Vuong Tan", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Kov\u00e1ts, D\u00e1vid", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Boldogh, S\u00e1ndor A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Corduneanu, Alexandra", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Sulyok, Kinga M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Gyuranecz, Mikl\u00f3s", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Kontsch\u00e1n, Jen\u0151", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Tak\u00e1cs, N\u00f3ra", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Halajian, Ali", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Epis, Sara", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Hofmann-Lehmann, Regina", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Africa", "Anaplasma", "Animals", "Arachnid Vectors", "Argasidae", "Asia", "Bacteria", "Bartonella", "Biodiversity", "Chiroptera", "Europe", "Haemoplasma", "Hard tick", "Mexico", "Polymerase Chain Reaction", "Rickettsia", "Sequence Analysis, DNA", "Soft tick", "Tick Infestations", "Biodiversity", "M